 battle has been waged for control of a mid-sized Ukrainian city. Why is Bakhmut an inflection point, and who stands to gain from its capture? Continue reading: Why is the city at a pivotal moment in its history?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:05:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/ng-interactive/2023/aug/10/how-bakhmut-became-a-pivot-in-the-ukraine-war" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mines-drone-strikes-organised-plan-to-export-ukraine-grain-via-danube-ports-is-no-easy-fix" target="_blank">Turning food into a weapon: how Russia resorted to one of the oldest forms of warfare</a></h2><div class="description"> With Russia blockading Ukraine’s eastern ports, an alternative route to the west is possible but faces serious problems. Moscow pulled out of an UN-brokered deal to allow Ukrainian grain exports through the Black Sea last month. The mining of the Kakhovka dam in June threatens to turn southern Ukrainian farmland into a dustbowl.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:47:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mines-drone-strikes-organised-plan-to-export-ukraine-grain-via-danube-ports-is-no-easy-fix" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/ukrainian-force-cross-dnipro-river-bid-breach-southern-frontline-kherson-city" target="_blank">Ukrainian forces cross Dnipro River in bid to breach southern frontline</a></h2><div class="description"> Up to seven boats landed east of Kherson city and broke through defensive lines, say Russian military bloggers. Ukrainian forces have made an attempt to cross the Dnipro River dividing liberated and occupied Kheron. The river has for months served as the frontline in the south of Ukraine.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:11:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/ukrainian-force-cross-dnipro-river-bid-breach-southern-frontline-kherson-city" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/how-learning-to-swim-at-60-set-me-free" target="_blank">‘Move forward. Flap around a little!’ How learning to swim at 60 set me free</a></h2><div class="description"> Years of chronic neck and back spasms had stolen all the variety and fun I used to find in working out, especially that amped-up endorphin high. By his early 50s, I had spent thousands of dollars trying to mitigate this pain with alternative treatments. I was told swimming would make me fit and strong-minded, but first I had to navigate the slow lane.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/how-learning-to-swim-at-60-set-me-free" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/dream-holiday-at-home-how-i-holidayed-in-venice-without-leaving-york" target="_blank">‘Soaked and shivering, I order a spritz’: how I holidayed in Venice – without leaving York</a></h2><div class="description"> Unable to get to Italy, I spent a day recreating a Venetian mini-break in my home town. Who needs the Grand Canal when you’ve got the Ouse? Thankfully I live in York, which is also very old and full of locals complaining about tourists.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/dream-holiday-at-home-how-i-holidayed-in-venice-without-leaving-york" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/make-mud-not-war-us-weather-warfare-vietnam-commando-lava-ho-chi-minh" target="_blank">‘Make mud, not war’: how US used weather warfare in Vietnam</a></h2><div class="description"> Top-secret project Commando Lava caused disruption along strategically vital Ho Chi Minh trail. US military weaponised this effect in an attempt to halt traffic on the strategically vital trail. The project had Hercules transport aircraft flying at low level to disperse powder engineered to turn mud into glutinous super-mud.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:00:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/make-mud-not-war-us-weather-warfare-vietnam-commando-lava-ho-chi-minh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/the-case-against-cosby-review-a-revelatory-story-from-the-woman-who-brought-him-down" target="_blank">The Case Against Cosby review – a revelatory story from the woman who brought him down</a></h2><div class="description"> This powerful film rails against a legal system that so often fails victims of sexual assault. It is a vivid, intimate – and ultimately redemptive – look at trauma. The Case Against Cosby is based on memoir written by Andrea Constand, who is the only woman able to gain a conviction against Cosby.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/the-case-against-cosby-review-a-revelatory-story-from-the-woman-who-brought-him-down" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/paul-mccartney-billy-joel-concerts-front-row-seats" target="_blank">‘Paul McCartney winked right at me’: the fans who buy nosebleed seats – and get whisked to the front</a></h2><div class="description"> Billy Joel has been playing one sold-out concert a month at Madison Square Garden for a decade. Joel said he wouldn't sell tickets to the front row because they were often sold at inflated prices to rich people. He said he'd see them "sitting there puffing on a cigar, ‘entertain me, piano man’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/paul-mccartney-billy-joel-concerts-front-row-seats" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/10/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-5-review-a-big-screen-inside-and-out" target="_blank">Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 5 review: a big screen inside and out</a></h2><div class="description"> The new Z Flip 5 costs £1,049 ($999/A$1,649) - £50 more than last year’s model. It comes with twice the starting storage and a collection of small but meaningful upgrades. The new flip phone has a bigger, more useful screen on the outside for its fifth generation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/10/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-5-review-a-big-screen-inside-and-out" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/10/wifedom-mrs-orwells-invisible-life-by-anna-funder-review-inside-a-troubled-marriage" target="_blank">Wifedom: Mrs Orwell’s Invisible Life by Anna Funder review – inside a troubled marriage</a></h2><div class="description"> This feminist reimagining of the fierce and witty Eileen O’Shaughnessy strips her of agency all over again. By the 1990s, the idea that the role of wife represented an aspect of patriarchal oppression was pervasive and uncontroversial. Hardly surprising: it had been a cornerstone of feminist thought ever since Charlotte Perkins Gilman lifted the lid on wifedom and servitude in 1898.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:30:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/10/wifedom-mrs-orwells-invisible-life-by-anna-funder-review-inside-a-troubled-marriage" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/painkiller-review-matthew-brodericks-character-is-just-evil" target="_blank">​​Painkiller review – Matthew Broderick’s character is just evil</a></h2><div class="description"> New Netflix drama series Painkiller is a similar to Disney+ drama Dopesick. Both are fictionalised accounts of real and composite people and events at the heart of the opioid epidemic. Both weave the story of one ‘typical’ individual’s gradual addiction to prescribed medication.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/painkiller-review-matthew-brodericks-character-is-just-evil" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/northern-ireland-data-breach-police-safety" target="_blank">We know the risks of policing Northern Ireland, but this data breach exposes us as never before | Andrew George</a></h2><div class="description"> Our surname and initials, as well as our place of work, were released into the public domain in a data breach that disclosed the details of 10,000 police officers and staff. The ongoing terrorist threat in Northern Ireland made the news hard to swallow. There are still some officers of different communities who do not divulge what they do for a living to protect themselves and those around them.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/northern-ireland-data-breach-police-safety" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/politics-independent-mps-westminster-voters-parties" target="_blank">In our polarised politics, there are no truly independent MPs – and Westminster is poorer for it | Martin Kettle</a></h2><div class="description"> For voters, the choice is still between the established parties. A more rational politics remains tantalisingly out of reach. To be an independent is very important in times deadened by orthodoxy. It matters just as much in times of polarisation, when those in the middle struggle to have a voice.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/politics-independent-mps-westminster-voters-parties" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/hs2-scrap-tories-labour-budget-public-finances" target="_blank">HS2 is the white elephant in the room. If the Tories won’t scrap it, Labour must | Larry Elliott</a></h2><div class="description"> The vanity project is scandalously over budget, years behind schedule and already pared back in a bid to save money. The new rail link between London and the north-west of England makes Concorde look like good value for money. A decision to stop throwing good money after bad is long overdue.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:00:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/hs2-scrap-tories-labour-budget-public-finances" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-strange-tale-of-the-crooked-house-tells-a-much-bigger-story" target="_blank">The strange tale of The Crooked House tells a much bigger story</a></h2><div class="description"> The Crooked House always lived large in the imagination of anyone from the West Midlands. It was the pub where things – marbles, coins, even people – rolled uphill. The first time you heard the words ‘optical’ and ‘illusion’ used together was in relation to the mysteries of the pub. Adrian Chiles is a broadcaster, writer and Guardian columnist.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:01:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-strange-tale-of-the-crooked-house-tells-a-much-bigger-story" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/09/steve-bell-on-lee-anderson-and-the-bibby-stockholm-barge-cartoon" target="_blank">Steve Bell on Lee Anderson and the Bibby Stockholm barge – cartoon</a></h2><div class="description"> CNN.com will feature iReporter photos in a weekly Travel Snapshots gallery. Please submit your best shots for next week's gallery of iReporters. Visit CNN iReport.com/Travel next Wednesday for a new gallery of snapshots of the world's most beautiful beaches.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:39:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/09/steve-bell-on-lee-anderson-and-the-bibby-stockholm-barge-cartoon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/donald-trump-prison-cell-campaign-for-us-president" target="_blank">Perverse as it sounds, Donald Trump in a prison cell may be the worst possible outcome | Emma Brockes</a></h2><div class="description"> Imagine Trump posing as the ultimate martyr, campaigning for president from jail – his supporters would find it irresistible. Trump is front and centre every day, but in danger of ascending to a new position in the news cycle: 'The ultimate martyr' He was still there, obviously, wandering the corridors at Mar-a-Lago and posting screeds.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:08:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/donald-trump-prison-cell-campaign-for-us-president" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-migrant-politics-margaret-thatcher-rishi-sunak" target="_blank">Lee Anderson’s vile anti-migrant comments pose this question: do we want politics like this? | Hugh Muir</a></h2><div class="description"> Lee Anderson, the deputy chair of the Conservative party, said asylum seekers should 'f*** off back to France' He was speaking to the Daily Express, with the knowledge that this once-great British newspaper now thrives on printing such things. Even Thatcher’s governments were above the hateful, toxic rhetoric now being favoured by Sunak and his lieutenants.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:21:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-migrant-politics-margaret-thatcher-rishi-sunak" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/narendra-modi-bjp-india-manipur-violence" target="_blank">Narendra Modi has ignored religious violence for too long. Now he must face the music | Priya Sharma</a></h2><div class="description"> Narendra Modi is accused of turning a blind eye to three months of bloodshed in some of the poorest villages of India. Hundreds of villages destroyed, Christian churches and schools torched, and widespread sexual assault of women. About 50,000 people have fled their homes; at least 124 are dead.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:24:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/narendra-modi-bjp-india-manipur-violence" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-electoral-commission-hack-democracy-needs-stronger-safeguards" target="_blank">The Guardian view on the electoral commission hack: democracy needs stronger safeguards | Editorial</a></h2><div class="description"> A culture of complacency around data security and a government obsessed with partisan games have put electoral regulation at risk. The security breach was only discovered last October and made public this week. The perpetrators have been identified as “hostile actors” which could be a criminal gang, a foreign state, or the former acting on behalf of the latter.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:34:09 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-electoral-commission-hack-democracy-needs-stronger-safeguards" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-amazon-summit-rich-nations-must-now-step-up" target="_blank">The Guardian view on the Amazon summit: rich nations must now step up</a></h2><div class="description"> Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva defeated Jair Bolsonaro by a margin of 1.8% in last October's election. The Amazon rainforest was hurtling towards a tipping point after which it would no longer function as a climate stabiliser. Deforestation dropped by 42% during Lula’s first seven months in office, and the state has returned as a protective state.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:34:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-amazon-summit-rich-nations-must-now-step-up" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-ugly-words-shame-britain" target="_blank">Lee Anderson’s ugly words shame Britain | Letters</a></h2><div class="description"> Alexandra Wright joined a march of silence from the library in Ladbroke Grove to Grenfell Tower. The Tory deputy chair used demeaning and disgusting language in his remarks about asylum seekers, she says. Plus letters from Kevin Potter and Will King, from Will King and Alexandra Wright.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:28:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-ugly-words-shame-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/views-from-both-sides-of-the-digital-divide" target="_blank">Views from both sides of the digital divide | Letters</a></h2><div class="description"> Josephine Culhane was nodding vigorously in agreement when she read your editorial. An hour later she was having a conversation with your subscription team about the fact that I could no longer have my subscription vouchers for the Guardian. I now need to use a barcode that would be scanned by my newsagent – in our only village shop. They do not have a scanner.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:28:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/views-from-both-sides-of-the-digital-divide" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/womens-world-cup-2023-last-16-power-rankings-england-france-australia-usa" target="_blank">Women’s World Cup power rankings: France on the rise, England drop down</a></h2><div class="description"> Japan continue to look the most in-form team in the competition. France, Australia, Spain and Colombia are all making upward moves. Hinata Miyazawa remains top scorer with five goals, equalling Homare Sawa’s Golden Boot-winning total in 2011.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:19:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/womens-world-cup-2023-last-16-power-rankings-england-france-australia-usa" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/lucy-bronze-england-unhappy-performances-womens-world-cup-colombia" target="_blank">Lucy Bronze admits England unhappy with performances and ‘can give more’</a></h2><div class="description"> England face Colombia in the World Cup quarter-final on Saturday. Lucy Bronze says England are 'not happy' with their performances. The Lionesses laboured against Nigeria, losing Lauren James to a red card for stepping on Michelle Alozie. It was the third time in four games that England have looked unconvincing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/lucy-bronze-england-unhappy-performances-womens-world-cup-colombia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/womens-world-cup-2023-france-vs-australia-squad-best-players-wendie-renard-kadidiatou-diani-vicki-becho-eugenie-le-sommer" target="_blank">Four France players who can break Australian hearts at the World Cup | Jack Snape</a></h2><div class="description"> Matildas take on France in World Cup quarter-final in Brisbane on Saturday. France started the tournament slowly before beating Brazil 2-1 and Panama 6-3. Since then, the world No 5-ranked side have been on a long journey. Sam Kerr's injury saga, Sam Kerr’s dour early victory over Ireland, defensive frailties against Nigeria, then the Matildaas’ revival.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:00:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/womens-world-cup-2023-france-vs-australia-squad-best-players-wendie-renard-kadidiatou-diani-vicki-becho-eugenie-le-sommer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/the-premier-league-is-back-for-an-uncluttered-if-uncertain-new-season" target="_blank">The Premier League is back for an uncluttered, if uncertain, new season | Barney Ronay</a></h2><div class="description"> A strange brew of noises off haunts the coming campaign, even if it offers a chance for English football to rediscover itself. The last time the Premier League enjoyed an untroubled, uninterrupted 38-game season Raheem Sterling ended up being voted PFA young player of the year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/the-premier-league-is-back-for-an-uncluttered-if-uncertain-new-season" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/anthony-joshua-random-drug-testing-boxing-dillian-whyte" target="_blank">Anthony Joshua calls for leading fighters to face random drug testing</a></h2><div class="description"> Anthony Joshua wants radical change to help tackle doping crisis. Joshua was meant to fight Dillian Whyte in London on Saturday night but his British rival has returned a positive test result for a still unnamed illegal substance. Whyte said he was “shocked and devastated” to learn of the test’s findings, while stating his innocence.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/anthony-joshua-random-drug-testing-boxing-dillian-whyte" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/non-league-football-season-ticket-sales-ashton-united-jonathan-sayer" target="_blank">‘Season-ticket sales remain on 14’: my ridiculous life running Ashton United</a></h2><div class="description"> Chairman orders and pays for new kits and training equipment for the forthcoming season. This includes home and away strips for both first teams, training wear plus kitbags. Dad decided to do the same so we now have double everything we need and have paid twice as much as we should have done.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/non-league-football-season-ticket-sales-ashton-united-jonathan-sayer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/sheffield-united-premier-league-2023-24-preview" target="_blank">Premier League 2023-24 preview No 17: Sheffield United</a></h2><div class="description"> Iliman Ndiaye is a massive blow to Paul Heckingbottom, who still has a large amount of players with Premier League experience. Daniel Jebbison will also look to youthful talent of Daniel Jebbison. The Championship side finished 2nd in the Championship last season.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 23:01:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/sheffield-united-premier-league-2023-24-preview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/emma-finucane-sprints-to-gold-but-katie-archibald-misses-out" target="_blank">Heartache for Katie Archibald but Emma Finucane sprints to gold</a></h2><div class="description"> Scot fails to claim medal in the women's Omnium in the UCI Cycling World Championships. Katie Archibald admits pressure of competing in the velodrome had been overwhelming. Scot missed out on the medals in the Omnium after failing to claim a gold medal.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:56:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/emma-finucane-sprints-to-gold-but-katie-archibald-misses-out" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/american-revolution-will-the-power-of-us-money-change-soccer-forever" target="_blank">American Revolution: will the power of US money change soccer forever?</a></h2><div class="description"> Messi is not, of course, the first aging superstar to put himself out to pasture on the gentle greens of US soccer. Pelé set the precedent, and many will follow once Messi has gone. The game is growing rapidly in America. But so is an awareness from those who see it as first and foremost as a business opportunity.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 08:00:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/american-revolution-will-the-power-of-us-money-change-soccer-forever" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/carabao-cup-roundup-afc-wimbledon-stun-coventry-to-earn-trip-to-chelsea" target="_blank">Carabao Cup roundup: AFC Wimbledon stun Coventry to earn trip to Chelsea</a></h2><div class="description"> AFC Wimbledon beat Coventry 2-1 in their Carabao Cup clash. Fulham will play Tottenham in an all-Premier League tie in the week commencing 28 August. Leeds to face Salford after overcoming Shrewsbury. Wimbledon to face Chelsea in the second round of the competition.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 22:04:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/carabao-cup-roundup-afc-wimbledon-stun-coventry-to-earn-trip-to-chelsea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/wembley-womens-challenge-cup-final-rugby-league-lois-forsell-leeds-st-helens" target="_blank">Wembley Challenge Cup final another giant step for women’s rugby league</a></h2><div class="description"> Women’s Challenge Cup final will take place at Wembley for the first time. Leeds Rhinos take on holders St Helens in a rematch of last year's decider. Leeds coach Lois Forsell: 'It's huge for future generations,’ says Forsell.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 13:23:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/wembley-womens-challenge-cup-final-rugby-league-lois-forsell-leeds-st-helens" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/lula-brazil-amazon-rainforests-money" target="_blank">‘Nature needs money’: Lula tells rich countries to pay up and protect world’s rainforests</a></h2><div class="description"> Brazilian president says developed nations that over centuries have pumped emissions into the atmosphere must ‘pay their bit’ Major rainforest nations demand hundreds of billions of dollars of climate financing and a greater role in how those resources are spent. Lula: “It’s not Brazil that needs money. It's not Colombia or Venezuela,” Lula says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:53:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/lula-brazil-amazon-rainforests-money" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/dam-partly-collapses-in-norway-as-storm-hans-continues-to-cause-chaos" target="_blank">Dam partly collapses in Norway as Storm Hans continues to cause chaos</a></h2><div class="description"> Parts of eastern and central Norway still on red alert as country battles widespread flooding and landslides. Police were considering blowing up the dam when water from the Glåma River, the country’s longest, started spilling out the side at Braskereidfoss hydroelectric power plant.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:32:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/dam-partly-collapses-in-norway-as-storm-hans-continues-to-cause-chaos" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/worlds-oldest-moss-could-go-extinct-as-a-result-of-climate-crisis" target="_blank">World’s oldest moss could go extinct as a result of climate crisis</a></h2><div class="description"> Takakia, 390m-year-old moss found in Himalayas, is at risk despite its ability to adapt to extreme weather. Takakia is one of the fastest-evolving species ever found, but that may not be enough to save it, scientists say.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:00:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/worlds-oldest-moss-could-go-extinct-as-a-result-of-climate-crisis" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/ai-helps-airline-pilots-avoid-areas-that-create-polluting-contrails" target="_blank">AI helps airline pilots avoid areas that create polluting contrails</a></h2><div class="description"> Experiment by Google and American Airlines reduces vapour trails, which are a source of global heating. Pilots flying using artificial intelligence models to choose different altitudes were able to reduce contrails by 54%. Further improvements are expected, Google said in a blogpost on Tuesday night.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:09:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/ai-helps-airline-pilots-avoid-areas-that-create-polluting-contrails" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/staffordshire-police-treating-fire-at-crooked-house-pub-as-arson" target="_blank">Staffordshire police treating fire at Crooked House pub as arson</a></h2><div class="description"> Blaze at famous pub nine days after it was sold to new owners sparked outrage and calls for it to be rebuilt. Police said they believed the fire ‘may have been started deliberately’ after fire investigators said the cause could “not currently be determined’.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:33:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/staffordshire-police-treating-fire-at-crooked-house-pub-as-arson" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/scottish-government-website-reveals-names-thousands-adopted-children" target="_blank">Thousands of adopted children’s names revealed on Scottish website</a></h2><div class="description"> Scotland's People site made available records of adoptions dating back 100 years. Records included the adopted child’s first name and new surname. Information Commissioner's Office has not received a formal breach report. National Records of Scotland (NRS) is an official arm of the Scottish government.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:34:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/scottish-government-website-reveals-names-thousands-adopted-children" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/hacked-uk-electoral-commission-data-target-voter-disinformation-warn-expert" target="_blank">Hacked UK voter data could be used to target disinformation, warn experts</a></h2><div class="description"> Data from Electoral Commission breach could allow rogue actors to create AI-generated messages in effort to manipulate elections. UK elections watchdog revealed on Tuesday that a hostile cyber-attack had been able to access the names and addresses of all voters registered between 2014 and 2022. State-backed actors could use the data to target voters with disinformation, experts have warned.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:21:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/hacked-uk-electoral-commission-data-target-voter-disinformation-warn-expert" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/labour-accuses-government-of-losing-250bn-from-value-of-uk-assets" target="_blank">Labour accuses government of losing £250bn from value of UK assets</a></h2><div class="description"> Labour accuse the government of ‘catastrophic financial mismanagement’ and claim it has ‘lost’ £251bn from the value of assets created to rescue the banking sector after the 2008 financial crash. Analysis of recently published figures showed a decline in value of the Bank of England’s assets – over which the Treasury acts as a guarantor – was a huge loss to taxpayers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:30:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/labour-accuses-government-of-losing-250bn-from-value-of-uk-assets" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/10/lotus-produce-record-2200-sports-cars-first-half-2023-eletre-electric-suv" target="_blank">Lotus produces record 2,200 sports cars in first half of 2023</a></h2><div class="description"> British carmaker also gearing up for sales of new Eletre electric SUV under Chinese owner Geely’s expansion plans. Lotus produced 2,200 vehicles in the first six months of the year at its factory in a former second world war bomber factory at Hethel in Norfolk.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 23:01:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/10/lotus-produce-record-2200-sports-cars-first-half-2023-eletre-electric-suv" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/oxford-street-shoppers-locked-in-stores-amid-social-media-robbery-campaign" target="_blank">Police in Oxford Street make arrests amid social media ‘robbery campaign’</a></h2><div class="description"> Hundreds of teenagers gathered outside JD Sports in response to Snapchat call to take part in robbery. Police have arrested nine people and issued dozens of dispersal orders after shoppers were locked inside stores on London’s busiest shopping street. Shoppers were locked in stores after warnings of a robbery campaign organised on social media.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/oxford-street-shoppers-locked-in-stores-amid-social-media-robbery-campaign" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/yorkshire-council-warns-of-budget-crisis-as-deficit-reaches-47m" target="_blank">Yorkshire council warns of budget crisis as deficit reaches £47m</a></h2><div class="description"> Kirklees local authority, hit by underfunding, price rises and extra demand on services, reports precarious finances. Growing number of local authorities warn they are almost running out of funds. Kirklees council, which counts Huddersfield as its main town, said it could face a section 114 notice in the 2024/25 financial year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:26:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/yorkshire-council-warns-of-budget-crisis-as-deficit-reaches-47m" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/four-of-britains-biggest-lenders-cut-rates-on-fixed-mortgage-deals" target="_blank">Four of Britain’s biggest lenders cut rates on fixed mortgage deals</a></h2><div class="description"> Halifax, HSBC, Nationwide and TSB reduce rates, easing pressure on hard-pressed homeowners. Halifax, part of Lloyds Banking Group – the UK’s biggest mortgage lender – is reducing rates by up to 0.71 percentage points from Friday. A five-year fixed rate currently priced at 6.10% will be offered at a rate of 5.39%.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:14:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/four-of-britains-biggest-lenders-cut-rates-on-fixed-mortgage-deals" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/hardeep-singh-kohli-comedian-charged-with-non-recent-sexual-offences" target="_blank">Comedian Hardeep Singh Kohli charged with non-recent sexual offences</a></h2><div class="description"> Scottish broadcaster arrested and released to appear in court at later date, say Police Scotland. Hardeep Singh Kohli charged in connection with non-recent sexual offences. Kohli, 54, has presented a number of programmes for the BBC, Channel 4, UKTV and other broadcasters.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:55:09 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/hardeep-singh-kohli-comedian-charged-with-non-recent-sexual-offences" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/twitter-fined-contempt-trump-case" target="_blank">US special counsel obtained search warrant for Trump’s Twitter account</a></h2><div class="description"> The US special counsel who is investigating Donald Trump obtained a search warrant for the former president’s Twitter account. Social media platform delayed complying, court filing shows, prompting judge to hold Twitter in contempt and fine it $350,000. The delay in compliance prompted a federal.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:09:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/twitter-fined-contempt-trump-case" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/us-voices-fears-for-niger-ex-president-who-is-running-out-of-food" target="_blank">US voices fears for Niger’s ex-president, who is ‘running out of food’</a></h2><div class="description"> Mohamed Bazoum, the West African nation’s democratically elected leader, has been held at the presidential palace in Niamey with his wife and son since July 26. His party said he and his family were running out of food and living under increasingly dire conditions.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:38:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/us-voices-fears-for-niger-ex-president-who-is-running-out-of-food" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/kim-jong-un-fires-dismisses-north-korea-top-military-general-pak-su-il" target="_blank">Kim Jong-un fires North Korea’s top general and calls for weapons production boost</a></h2><div class="description"> Leader replaces Pak Su-il with defence minister, Gen Ri Yong-gil, and urges further military drills. Kim Jong-un calls for more preparations for possibility of war, boost in weapons production and expansion of drills. It remains unclear if Ri will retain his role as defence minister.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 00:42:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/kim-jong-un-fires-dismisses-north-korea-top-military-general-pak-su-il" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/argentina-election-campaigns-suspended-girl-killed-buenos-aires" target="_blank">Argentina election campaigns suspended after 11-year old killed in robbery</a></h2><div class="description"> Morena Domínguez was attacked by two robbers riding a motorcycle in Lanús, Buenos Aires. The 11-year-old was about to arrive at school early on Wednesday morning in the Buenos Aires district. The attackers snatched her mobile phone, and she fell to the pavement where she was left unconscious.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:25:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/argentina-election-campaigns-suspended-girl-killed-buenos-aires" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/rust-shooting-halyna-hutchins-hannah-gutierrez-reed-trial-case-death" target="_blank">Rust film shooting: weapons supervisor pleads not guilty to involuntary manslaughter</a></h2><div class="description"> Hannah Gutierrez Reed has pleaded not guilty to involuntary manslaughter and evidence tampering charges in the shooting death of Halyna Hutchins. New Mexico district court judge Mary Sommer has set the trial to run 6 to 15 December. Hutchins was cinematographer on set of Alec Baldwin film.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:04:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/rust-shooting-halyna-hutchins-hannah-gutierrez-reed-trial-case-death" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/biden-executive-order-us-investment-chinese-technology" target="_blank">Biden bans range of US high tech investments in China citing national security risk</a></h2><div class="description"> The order – to be implemented next year – restricts investments in semiconductors and microelectronics, quantum tech and AI. The long-awaited order authorises the US treasury secretary to prohibit or restrict certain US investments in Chinese entities in three sectors. The order will require government notification of funding in other tech sectors.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:54:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/biden-executive-order-us-investment-chinese-technology" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/utah-man-killed-biden-visit-assassination-threat" target="_blank">FBI agents shoot and kill Utah man accused of making threats against Biden</a></h2><div class="description"> Agents were trying to serve warrant on Craig Deleeuw Robertson’s home hours before president was expected to land in state. Special agents shot and killed Robertson in Provo, Utah, when shooting happened at 6.15am on Wednesday. Robertson was accused of making threats against Joe Biden.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:49:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/utah-man-killed-biden-visit-assassination-threat" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mexico-president-amlo-gender-based-violence" target="_blank">Mexico: outrage as Amlo suggests critics guilty of ‘gender-based violence’ against him</a></h2><div class="description"> Comments touched a nerve in Mexico, where the government has been unable to tackle soaring levels of violence against women. A resurgent feminist movement has become a thorn in the president’s side. López Obrador's comments prompt condemnation in country with soaring level of violence.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:58:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mexico-president-amlo-gender-based-violence" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/ohio-issue-1-abortion-rights-win" target="_blank">‘Ohio saw through the con’: abortion rights advocates celebrate Issue 1 result</a></h2><div class="description"> Ohio voters rejected Issue 1, a GOP-backed ballot measure that would have made it considerably harder to amend the state constitution. Issue 1 means Ohio keeps its longstanding rule on citizen-led state constitutional amendments: a simple majority of state voters can change the constitution through a ballot measure.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:53:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/ohio-issue-1-abortion-rights-win" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/mammoth-mountain-california-ski-season-ends" target="_blank">Ski season finally ends at California’s Mammoth Mountain resort</a></h2><div class="description"> The ski lifts at Mammoth Mountain, in the eastern Sierra Nevadas, have been open since early November. It was one of the longest seasons in resort’s 70-year history, helped out by a colossal snowpack from an extreme weather winter. The sheer amount of snow the mountain saw made this season exceptional.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 22:30:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/mammoth-mountain-california-ski-season-ends" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/the-band-robbie-robertson-captured-a-dream-of-what-america-was-is-and-might-be" target="_blank">The Band’s Robbie Robertson captured a dream of what America was, is and might be | Michael Hann</a></h2><div class="description"> The bandleader who didn’t front his band, who was never as celebrated as Bob Dylan or their peers, was the glue keeping the Band together. Robertson was fortunate to have Levon Helm, Rick Danko and Richard Manuel to interpret the songs he wrote for the Band.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 01:05:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/the-band-robbie-robertson-captured-a-dream-of-what-america-was-is-and-might-be" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2023/aug/10/artists-using-artificial-intelligence-science-gallery" target="_blank">Meet the artists reclaiming AI from big tech – with the help of cats, bees and drag queens</a></h2><div class="description"> AI’s potential is huge and terrifying, but a new generation of artists is starting to find new uses for the technology. For these AI-generated drag kings and queens, life really is a cabaret. Between each song, the performers underwent a kind of metamorphosis, melting down into amorphous masses of pixels and then re-forming.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2023/aug/10/artists-using-artificial-intelligence-science-gallery" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/ben-target-lorenzo-review-summerhall-edinburgh" target="_blank">Ben Target: Lorenzo review – end-of-life care comedy is joyful and surprising</a></h2><div class="description"> Ben Target relives being a carer for a lovably eccentric adopted uncle in a heartfelt show that demonstrates caring’s reciprocal flow. The show flits between timelines to recount the relationship with Lorenzo, a fugitive from a rackety Hong Kong upbringing. Lorenzo was a maverick live-in colleague of his grandparents and “the only adult [Target] ever felt safe”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:42:07 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/ben-target-lorenzo-review-summerhall-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/two-doors-down-creator-simon-carlyle-dies" target="_blank">Two Doors Down creator Simon Carlyle dies aged 48</a></h2><div class="description"> Simon Carlyle hailed as ‘major comedic talent’ who also worked on Changing Ends and Boy Meets Girl. His manager, Amanda Davis, said he was known for being supportive and collaborative with other creators. Two Doors Down creator hailed as 'brilliant, funny, mercurial and magnificent'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:54:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/two-doors-down-creator-simon-carlyle-dies" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/10/strangers-at-the-port-by-lauren-aimee-curtis-review-an-island-controlled-by-men" target="_blank">Strangers at the Port by Lauren Aimee Curtis review – an island controlled by men</a></h2><div class="description"> Strangers at the Port by Lauren Aimee Curtis is set on an island where patriarchy has gone beyond realism. The island is unnamed but firmly located near Sicily by reference to The Odyssey and the Napoleonic War. The historical setting at first seems unsettled. Subsistence farming, homespun clothes and lo-tech living suggest a range of several centuries.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 08:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/10/strangers-at-the-port-by-lauren-aimee-curtis-review-an-island-controlled-by-men" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/come-together-the-democracy-of-the-symphony-musics-greatest-form-emily-macregor" target="_blank">Come together: the democracy of the symphony – music’s greatest form?</a></h2><div class="description"> The real – and symbolic – power of the symphony has held composers in thrall for over 200 years. Beethoven’s Symphony No 3, known as the Eroica (Heroic), is the canonic centrepiece of the Proms. The programme also features a symphonic gem composed by Croatian Dora Pejačević.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:49:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/come-together-the-democracy-of-the-symphony-musics-greatest-form-emily-macregor" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">From Pig Beach to Dunn’s River Falls: 10 must-visit Caribbean destinations – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is home to the world’s best beaches, pretty towns, waterfalls and national parks. There are stunning marine life, the best beaches and pretty towns in the world's most beautiful places. Here's the Caribbean in all its glory, including some pretty towns and waterfalls.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:35:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">From snorkelling to surfing: nine must-try Caribbean beach and water activities</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean offers a huge variety of tempting activities from snorkelling to scuba diving. Windsurfing and waterskiing is a must-try activity for everyone. The Exu Exu is one of the Caribbean’s most beautiful, vividly coloured coral reefs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:38:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Nightlife, loveseats and beautiful beaches: why the Caribbean makes for the perfect romantic holiday</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is an unbeatable destination for a romantic getaway with your loved one. From Jamaica to the hidden gem that is Curaçao, there’s something to suit every couple, whether on honeymoon, celebrating an anniversary, or just escaping everyday life for a taste of luxury.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:37:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Waterfalls, history and the world’s first underwater sculpture park: seven exciting things to do in the Caribbean</a></h2><div class="description"> The islands of the Caribbean are like nowhere else on Earth. From cocktails to coral reefs, they offer something for all tastes and tempos. Enjoy a classic mojito or piña colada on the white sand beaches of Barbados or Jamaica. Explore the area’s rich history and natural beauty.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:36:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/council-refused-to-pay-full-cost-of-replacing-two-pothole-damaged-tyres" target="_blank">Council refused to pay full cost of replacing two pothole-damaged tyres</a></h2><div class="description"> Reading borough council admitted breach of duty but deducted 30% from claim. Council insurance does not include ‘betterment’ - replacing old items with new. Unless you can produce receipts showing that the damaged tyres had been bought very recently, the council will deduct a sum from a claim.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/council-refused-to-pay-full-cost-of-replacing-two-pothole-damaged-tyres" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/literary-dorset-pj-harvey-thomas-hardy-william-barnes" target="_blank">Of Thomas Hardy and PJ Harvey: on the trail of Dorset’s inspirational powers</a></h2><div class="description"> The county’s people, landscapes and villages have provided material for generations of writers. Thomas Hardy stamped his personality over his idea of Wessex, reviving an ancient kingdom and giving towns and villages new names. Every town seems to have been a film set for a Hardy adaptation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/literary-dorset-pj-harvey-thomas-hardy-william-barnes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/hiking-relationships-family-dating" target="_blank">What I learned from hiking with a partner who strode ahead – and wouldn’t slow down</a></h2><div class="description"> In our 20s, we’d trekked for three months in Nepal, only stopping to sip hot chai and eat warm dal for meals. After serving in the Peace Corps in the Central African Republic, I'd anticipated a romantic journey as a couple with my best friend turned boyfriend. But as hiking partners, we were rarely together.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/hiking-relationships-family-dating" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/3967-steps-a-day-the-new-magic-number-for-a-healthy-happy-life" target="_blank">3,967 steps a day: the new magic number for a healthy, happy life?</a></h2><div class="description"> The very thought of exercise can be tiring, but don't despair. Small changes can make a big difference to your body. Walking has been around 300m to 400m years since our ancestors replaced fins and gills with legs. It is thought that our ancestors have been walking for 300m years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:05:18 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/3967-steps-a-day-the-new-magic-number-for-a-healthy-happy-life" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/how-to-make-the-perfect-vegan-moussaka-recipe-felicity-cloake" target="_blank">How to make the perfect vegan moussaka – recipe | Felicity Cloake's How to make the perfect ...</a></h2><div class="description"> Our in-house perfectionist scours Greece and the Levant for the best of the best vegan versions of this much-loved layer bake. Even in Greece, the 200-odd fasting days a year mandated by the Orthodox church mean that plant-based cuisine is more common than the casual visitor surviving on souvlaki and sea bass.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/how-to-make-the-perfect-vegan-moussaka-recipe-felicity-cloake" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/no-swearing-no-singing-no-fancy-dress-uks-strictest-pub-calls-time" target="_blank">No swearing, no singing, no fancy dress: UK’s ‘strictest pub’ calls time</a></h2><div class="description"> Landlord Shaun Collinge has run the York pub for 31 years and says the rules are harder to enforce post-pandemic. Rules include: no swearing, no singing, no television, no music, no stag parties, no hen dos and no fancy dress.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:55:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/no-swearing-no-singing-no-fancy-dress-uks-strictest-pub-calls-time" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then, 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/tell-us-whats-your-experience-with-buy-now-pay-later-schemes-in-the-uk" target="_blank">Tell us: what’s your experience with buy now, pay later schemes in the UK?</a></h2><div class="description"> Buy no, pay later schemes like Klarna and Clearpay have surged in recent years. People in the UK spent £5.6bn in the first six months of 2022 alone. 49% of people of those with a BNPL loan find it difficult to keep up with household bills.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:16:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/tell-us-whats-your-experience-with-buy-now-pay-later-schemes-in-the-uk" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">UK students: do you plan to live at home during university?</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 90% of higher education students say they are worried about the rising cost of living. We want to speak to students who are considering living at home this year. Are you planning to commute in? Or are you going to live on campus? Are there other ways you plan on saving costs?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:33:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">UK workers: are you struggling to get the hours you’d like to work?</a></h2><div class="description"> We want to hear from ‘underemployed’ workers who are not getting as much work as they’d like. Whether you’ve had trouble finding full time work, have had shifts cancelled regularly or have had your hours reduced permanently by your employer since you signed up for the job.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:27:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/share-your-experience-of-travelling-outside-the-uk-for-ivf" target="_blank">Share your experience of travelling outside the UK for IVF</a></h2><div class="description"> People in the UK are increasingly funding IVF treatments privately, research shows. 63% of IVF funded privately in 2021 compared to 52% in 2019. IVF cycles funded by the NHS saw a decrease to 20,000 in 2021 from around 24,000. We want to hear from people who have travelled abroad for fertility treatments.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:05:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/share-your-experience-of-travelling-outside-the-uk-for-ivf" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/audio/2023/aug/10/the-quran-burnings-in-sweden-who-is-fanning-the-flames-podcast" target="_blank">The Qur’an burnings in Sweden: who is fanning the flames? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The act of burning a holy book in Sweden is not of itself illegal. But a spate of burnings has resulted in outrage at home and abroad – and potentially far-reaching consequences. Sweden is facing diplomatic pressure from the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation, which represents 57 countries. At the same time it is fretting over the support of Turkey to allow it to become a full Nato member.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 02:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/audio/2023/aug/10/the-quran-burnings-in-sweden-who-is-fanning-the-flames-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/10/summer-picks-are-we-any-closer-to-understanding-long-covid-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: are we any closer to understanding long Covid? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Ian Sample hears from Scotland’s Astronomer Royal, Prof Catherine Heymans, about her experience of long Covid and how it has affected her life. He also speaks to Prof Danny Altmann, an immunologist at Imperial College London, about the scientific understanding of the condition.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/10/summer-picks-are-we-any-closer-to-understanding-long-covid-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/09/why-the-rest-of-the-world-cant-afford-to-ignore-the-coup-in-niger-podcast" target="_blank">Why the rest of the world can’t afford to ignore the coup in Niger – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The Sahel region, sometimes called Africa’s ‘coup belt’ has just seen another government ousted. The eighth overthrow of a government in the region in the past three years and may be the most significant. Peter Beaumont and Nesrine Malik on what it means for African – and global – security.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/09/why-the-rest-of-the-world-cant-afford-to-ignore-the-coup-in-niger-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/08/colombia-set-up-quarter-final-with-england-womens-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Colombia set up quarter-final with England – Women’s Football Weekly</a></h2><div class="description"> Colombia beat Jamaica 1-0 to reach their first ever quarter-final, where they will face England. Faye Carruthers is joined by Suzy Wrack, Sophie Downey and Jonathan Liew as the round of 16 comes to a close. We also bid farewell to the Reggae Girlz, who became the first Caribbean nation to play in knockout stages of a World Cup, male or female, since Cuba in 1938.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:47:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/08/colombia-set-up-quarter-final-with-england-womens-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">The legacy of Sinéad O’Connor – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Kathryn Ferguson and journalist Simon Hattenstone share their memories of Sinéad O'Connor. Ferguson directed Nothing Compares, a 2022 documentary about the singer's life. She explains why O’Connor spoke out about abuse in the Catholic church in the early 1990s when it was still taboo to do so.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/10/our-history-is-rotting-away-the-newspaper-archivists-preserving-nigerias-past" target="_blank">‘Our history is rotting away’: the newspaper archivists preserving Nigeria’s past</a></h2><div class="description"> PM News was founded in 1994 but stopped printing physical copies in 2015. Project will be Nigeria’s first interactive digital newspaper archive. More than 50,000 pages of PM News will be saved for posterity by an ambitious archive project. The project is based in Lekki, an affluent suburb of Lagos, Nigeria.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">Th